ZH: 他不愿意成为一个只会袖手旁观的人。
EN: He doesn't want to be a person who just stands by and watches.

ZH: 面对冲突，我们不能袖手旁观。
EN: We cannot stand by and watch when facing conflicts.

ZH: 只袖手旁观会导致问题进一步恶化。
EN: Just standing by and watching will lead to further deterioration of the problem.

ZH: 当局应该采取行动，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: The authorities should take action instead of standing idly by.

ZH: 每个人都应该对社会问题负起责任，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: Everyone should take responsibility for social problems instead of being a bystander.

ZH: 我们不能让不正义的事情发生，然后只是袖手旁观。
EN: We cannot let injustices happen and then just be indifferent.

ZH: 在这个艰难的时刻，我们不能袖手旁观。
EN: In this difficult moment, we cannot stand by and do nothing.

ZH: 我们需要有力地回应，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: We need to respond strongly instead of being passive bystanders.

ZH: 袖手旁观是不负责任的行为。
EN: Standing idly by is an irresponsible behavior.

ZH: 我不会只是袖手旁观，我会尽力帮助你。
EN: I won't just stand by and watch, I will do my best to help you.

ZH: 我们应该团结起来，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: We should unite instead of standing by and doing nothing.

ZH: 当别人需要帮助时，我们不能只是袖手旁观。
EN: We cannot just stand by when someone needs help.

ZH: 我们应该大声说出不公正的事情，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: We should speak out loud about injustices instead of turning a blind eye.

ZH: 这个社会需要我们积极参与，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: This society needs our active participation instead of our indifference.

ZH: 我们不能对周围的问题无动于衷，而只是袖手旁观。
EN: We cannot be indifferent to the problems around us and just stand by.

ZH: 作为公民，我们有责任参与改变，而不是袖手旁观。
EN: As citizens, we have the responsibility to engage in change instead of standing idly by.

ZH: 在这个关键时刻，我们不能袖手旁观。
EN: In this crucial moment, we cannot just stand by and watch.

ZH: 袖手旁观会让不公正的现象更加猖獗。
EN: Standing idly by will only allow injustices to spread more widely.

ZH: 我们应该积极地参与改变，不要只是袖手旁观。
EN: We should actively participate in change instead of just being bystanders.

ZH: 袖手旁观是对问题的漠视。
EN: Standing by and watching is indifference towards the problem.
